==========
Installing
==========

INSTALLATION

Dependencies are:
* python (version 2.6 or higher) - e.g. http://www.python.org/download/releases/2.7.1/
* pyOSC - http://gitorious.org/pyosc (checkout included in the packaged version)
* pyserial (version 2.5 or higher) - http://pyserial.sourceforge.net/ - download: http://sourceforge.net/projects/pyserial/files/pyserial/2.5/pyserial-2.5.tar.gz/download

python :
check which version you have:
  $ python --version
If it is lower than 2.6 you will need to get a version higher than 2.6.

Install the dependencies:

pyOSC :
  $ cd pyosc
  $ sudo ./setup.py install

pyserial:
Follow the instructions at:
  http://pyserial.sourceforge.net/pyserial.html#installation


(proper setup script for pydon itself to follow)

==========

go to the hive directory
  $ cd hive
  
start:
  $ python swpydonhive.py
  
this will print the help:

Usage: swpydonhive.py [options]

Create a datanetwork client to communicate with the minibee network.

Options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -p PORT, --port=PORT  the port on which the client will listen
                        [default:57600]
  -n NAME, --name=NAME  the name of the client in the datanetwork
                        [default:pydonhive]
  -c CONFIG, --config=CONFIG
                        the name of the configuration file for the minibees
                        [default:hiveconfig.xml]
  -m MINIBEES, --nr_of_minibees=MINIBEES
                        the number of minibees in the network [default:10]
  -d HOST, --host_ip=HOST
                        the ip address of the datanetwork host
                        [default:127.0.0.1]
  -s SERIAL, --serial=SERIAL
                        the serial port [default:/dev/ttyUSB0]

